'''湯博區'''（{{lang-en|Tombaugh Regio}}，俗稱'''冥王星之心'''）是[[矮行星|矮行星]][[冥王星|冥王星]]一個顯著的表面特徵。<ref name="verge20150715">{{cite web|last1 = O'Kane|first1 = Sean|title = This is the first high resolution image of Plutos' surface|url = http://www.theverge.com/2015/7/15/8972271/nasa-new-horizons-new-pluto-image|website = The Verge|accessdate = 15 July 2015|date = 15 July 2015|archive-date = 2019-01-05|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190105024112/https://www.theverge.com/2015/7/15/8972271/nasa-new-horizons-new-pluto-image|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="nbc20150715">{{cite web|last1 = Coldewey|first1 = Devin|title = Latest New Horizons Photo Shows Close-Up of Pluto's Young Mountains|url = http://www.nbcnews.com/science/space/pluto-photo-n392691|website = NBC News|publisher = Comcast|accessdate = 15 July 2015|date = 15 July 2015|archive-date = 2018-06-21|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180621030222/https://www.nbcnews.com/science/space/pluto-photo-n392691|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="nyt20150715">{{cite web|last1 = The New York Times|title = New Horizons Reveals Ice Mountains on Pluto|url = http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2015/07/15/science/space/new-horizons-pluto-flyby-photos.html?_r=1|website = The New York Times|accessdate = 15 July 2015|date = 15 July 2015|archive-date = 2019-02-07|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190207214602/https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2015/07/15/science/space/new-horizons-pluto-flyby-photos.html?_r=1|dead-url = no}}</ref>一個橫跨大約1,590公里的巨大、淺色區域，<ref name="whale">{{cite web|last1 = Feltman|first1 = Rachel|title = New map of Pluto reveals a ‘whale’ and a ‘donut’|url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2015/07/08/new-map-of-pluto-reveals-a-whale-and-a-donut/|publisher = The Washington Post|accessdate = 14 July 2015|date = 8 July 2015|archive-date = 2019-05-27|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190527073230/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2015/07/08/new-map-of-pluto-reveals-a-whale-and-a-donut/|dead-url = no}}</ref>在[[NASA|NASA]]的媒體當中被暱稱為冥王星的“'''心'''”。<ref>[http://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2015/07/14/new-data-reveals-that-plutos-heart-is-broken/ New data reveals that Pluto's heart is broken] {{Wayback|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2015/07/14/new-data-reveals-that-plutos-heart-is-broken/ |date=20170905000735 }}.</ref><ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/projects/cp/summer-of-science-2015/latest/nasa-pluto-image-release Coming today: a close-up of Pluto's heart] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/projects/cp/summer-of-science-2015/latest/nasa-pluto-image-release |date=20171128233543 }}.</ref><ref>[https://www.nasa.gov/feature/new-horizons-spacecraft-displays-pluto-s-big-heart-0 New Horizons spacecraft displays Pltuo's big heart] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nasa.gov/feature/new-horizons-spacecraft-displays-pluto-s-big-heart-0 |date=20150716112542 }}.</ref>

該區域首次被發現是在[[新视野号|新视野号]]探測器從異常進入的安全模式恢復後，由冥王星所傳回來的初始影像。NASA最初依照其整體外型輪廓而稱為“心”。<ref>{{cite web|title = NASA’s New Horizons: A “Heart” from Pluto as Flyby Begins|url = https://www.nasa.gov/feature/nasa-s-new-horizons-a-heart-from-pluto-as-flyby-begins|publisher = NASA|accessdate = 15 July 2015|date = 8 July 2015|archive-date = 2019-04-03|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190403195019/https://www.nasa.gov/feature/nasa-s-new-horizons-a-heart-from-pluto-as-flyby-begins/|dead-url = no}}</ref>2015年7月15日，這個區域被NASA正式命名為“'''湯博區'''”，以紀念冥王星的發現者-天文學家[[克莱德·汤博|克莱德·汤博]]。<ref name="verge20150715"/>儘管如此，NASA仍舊會使用“心”來稱呼這個區域<ref name=Sky&Telescope>{{cite web|title=Pluto and Charon Dazzle with Diversity|author=Kelly Beatty|publisher=Popular Mechanics|year=2015|accessdate=2015-07-16|url=http://www.skyandtelescope.com/astronomy-news/pluto-and-charon-dazzle-with-diversity-07162015/|archive-date=2015-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150720185738/http://www.skyandtelescope.com/astronomy-news/pluto-and-charon-dazzle-with-diversity-07162015/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

稍後收集到的資料顯示，“心”的兩“葉”雖然共同有一個明亮的外觀，但相鄰的地質特性卻截然不同。左葉的部分比右葉來得平滑，顏色也有些微不同。<ref name="brokenheart">{{cite web|last1 = Feltman|first1 = Rachel|title = New data reveals that Pluto’s heart is broken|url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2015/07/14/new-data-reveals-that-plutos-heart-is-broken/|publisher = The Washington Post|accessdate = 14 July 2015|date = 14 July 2015|archive-date = 2017-09-05|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170905000735/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2015/07/14/new-data-reveals-that-plutos-heart-is-broken/|dead-url = no}}</ref>在早先的猜想，左葉是被氮雪填滿的巨大隕石坑，當中的亮點則是突出的山峰。<ref name="arrives">{{cite web|last1 = Achenbach|first1 = Joel|title = New Horizons reaches Pluto, sees complex terrain with ‘great mounds’|url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/national/health-science/new-horizons-finally-makes-it-to-pluto-sees-craters-and-great-mounds/2015/07/14/9bcb0f04-2a1f-11e5-bd33-395c05608059_story.html|publisher = The Washington Post|accessdate = 14 July 2015|date = 14 July 2015|archive-date = 2015-07-15|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150715111854/http://www.washingtonpost.com/national/health-science/new-horizons-finally-makes-it-to-pluto-sees-craters-and-great-mounds/2015/07/14/9bcb0f04-2a1f-11e5-bd33-395c05608059_story.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>7月15日公開的照片顯示了當中有3,500公尺高，由水冰形成的山脈。在“心”底部的深暗區域，似乎可能是一個含有大量冰的撞擊坑，而“水冰山脈”是碰撞的殘餘碎片，“湯博區”的平滑特徵則是碰撞後安定的殘餘。

在新視野號所得到最初的相片中，平滑的表面缺乏撞擊坑，顯示該大撞擊在冥王星的行星形成中是“近期”發生的。從這種巨大的撞擊產生的熱，可能是行星碰撞的交互作用中仍無法解釋的能量儲存。這樣撞擊的巨大力量可以解釋一些冥王星表面所看到的地質特徵，同時也有助於進一步解釋其他目前尚未了解的地貌過程。<ref>{{cite web|last1 = Orwig|first1 = Jessica|title = The first insanely close-up photos of Pluto reveal water on its surface|url = http://www.businessinsider.com/the-first-insanely-close-up-photos-of-pluto-reveal-water-on-its-surface-2015-7|publisher = Business Insider|accessdate = 15 July 2015|date = 15 July 2015|archive-date = 2016-05-09|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160509013704/http://www.businessinsider.com/the-first-insanely-close-up-photos-of-pluto-reveal-water-on-its-surface-2015-7|dead-url = no}}</ref>

這個特徵在新視野號穿越的60年前已經被辨認為是一個亮點，雖然在當時仍不可能有足夠的解析度來確定它的形狀。<ref>{{cite web|first1 = Christopher|last1 = Crockett|title = Mission to Pluto: Live coverage: Sitting and speculating|url = https://www.sciencenews.org/article/mission-pluto-live-coverage#heart|publisher = Science News|accessdate = 15 July 2015|date = 14 July 2015|archive-date = 2016-05-27|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160527142129/https://www.sciencenews.org/article/mission-pluto-live-coverage#heart|dead-url = no}}</ref>

有些人也認為這個特徵看起來像是[[迪士尼|迪士尼]]當中與冥王星同名的角色——[[布鲁托|布鲁托]]。<ref>{{cite web|title=Does Pluto's bright spot look more like a heart or the Disney dog?|url=http://www.baynews9.com/content/news/baynews9/on-the-town/article.html/content/news/articles/cfn/2015/7/14/pluto_flyby_heart_or_dog.html|website=baynews9.com|author=Mike Westfall|date=14 July 2015|accessdate=2015-07-16|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716130338/http://www.baynews9.com/content/news/baynews9/on-the-town/article.html/content/news/articles/cfn/2015/7/14/pluto_flyby_heart_or_dog.html|archivedate=2015-07-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=New Horizons Space Probe: Pluto Gets the Meme Treatment|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/horizons-pluto-meme-treatment/story?id=32447208|website=abcnews|author=ALYSSA NEWCOMB|date=14 July 2015|accessdate=2015-07-16|archive-date=2015-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716161613/http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/horizons-pluto-meme-treatment/story?id=32447208|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The best Pluto memes. Well done, internet|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/33535721/the-best-pluto-memes-well-done-internet|website=BBC|accessdate=16 July 2015|archive-date=2015-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150718020544/http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/33535721/the-best-pluto-memes-well-done-internet|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此外，該特徵也意外地與[[美少女戰士|美少女戰士]]的[[水手冥王星|水手冥王星]]的武器時空之杖上可分離的石榴石外型相似。

